{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-recipe-page-js","path":"/mapo-tofu/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Chez Nosredna"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b9465d5b-fdd6-5e94-bff1-4f5caefbca05","excerpt":"See the video description for directions.  The mushrooms supply the essential umami that this dish requires (it’s normally very meaty), so make sure you do…","html":"<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/2i1UFiDY61U\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<p>See the video description for directions. </p>\n<p>The mushrooms supply the essential umami that this dish requires (it’s normally very meaty), so make sure you do justice by the mushrooms.</p>\n<p>I’ve indicated in my notes where I deviated from the original ingredients, either out of necessity, or fear. The result was really good, and near the edge of our comfort zone (heatwise).</p>\n<p>The original suggests substituting black peppercorns for Sichuan peppercorns, if you must. That would be sad.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Mapo Tofu","date":"December 13, 2020","description":"A vegan version on this intensely spicy classic","prep":"20 mins","cook":"30 mins","servings":"3-4","tags":["Main","Chinese","Vegan(ish)"],"tools":null,"ingredients":[{"ingredient":"4 dried shiitake mushrooms","note":"I used black fungus"},{"ingredient":"2 1/2 cups water","note":null},{"ingredient":"3 green onions","note":null},{"ingredient":"1 cup canned chickpeas","note":null},{"ingredient":"1 lb soft or medium firm tofu","note":null},{"ingredient":"2 cloves garlic","note":null},{"ingredient":"1 small piece ginger","note":null},{"ingredient":"1-2 tsp Sichuan peppercorns","n